ce:section.ce:para:
Zeta potential measurements of NCQDs samples in an aqueous medium confirm the formation of amine and carboxylic functional groups (Fig. 8
                           ). As a reference value, CQDs (without N-doping) have a negative potential (−17.4 mV) due mainly to the -COO− groups (Figure S2). By contrast, the zeta potential of NCQDs is positive (+5.4 mV) primarily due to the NH3
                           + groups generated by the protonation of NH2 in aqueous solution (top of Fig. 8, red line). These zeta potential values suggest that the materials have colloidal stability and solubility in an aqueous solution [52]. The positive potential of NCQDs changed to negative potentials (−15 mV) for NCQDs/CYS (bottom of Fig. 8, blue line), which is attributed to the negative charge of thiolate group of l-cysteine in an aqueous medium and confirms the presence of l-cysteine on the NCQDs surface.
